declarations.comments:
A two-dimensional Matrix. Its Show instance is meant as a tool for
debugging/pretty-printing.
declarations.title: Matrix

declarations.comments: Returns the height of a matrix.
declarations.title: height

declarations.comments: Returns the width of a matrix.
declarations.title: width

declarations.comments:
Repeats the same value and creates a width Ã— height `Matrix`.

```purescript
> repeat 2 3 "X"
"X", "X"
"X", "X"
"X", "X"
```
declarations.title: repeat

declarations.comments: Checks whether a Matrix is empty
declarations.title: isEmpty

declarations.comments:
Constructs a Matrix from an Array of Arrays. Returns `Nothing` if the
dimensions don't line up.

```purescript
> fromMaybe empty (fromArray [[1,2,3], [4,5,6]])
1, 2, 3
4, 5, 6

> fromArray [[1,2,3], [4,5]]
Nothing
```
declarations.title: fromArray

declarations.comments:
Returns the value at column, row or `Nothing` if the index was out of
bounds.
declarations.title: get

declarations.comments:
Sets the value at column, row or returns `Nothing` if the index was out of
bounds.
declarations.title: set

declarations.comments:
Applies the given function to the element at column, row or returns Nothing
if the index was out of bounds.
declarations.title: modify

declarations.comments: Get the row at the given index.
declarations.title: getRow

declarations.comments: Get the column at the given index.
declarations.title: getColumn

declarations.comments: Convert a `Matrix` to an indexed Array
declarations.title: toIndexedArray

declarations.comments:
Apply a function to every element in the given Matrix taking its indices
into account
declarations.title: indexedMap

declarations.comments:
Combines two Matrices with the same dimensions by combining elements at the
same index with the given function. Returns Nothing on a dimension
mismatch.
declarations.title: zipWith

declarations.comments: Pretty prints a matrix using the given formatting function on every element
declarations.title: prettyPrintMatrix
